Here’s the second module—**Part 2: Spark Overview**—from the Lumina Spark intro sequence:

videoYour Lumina Spark Part 2: Spark Overviewturn1search0

This module dives into the full Lumina Spark model, covering:

- The **four colour energies** (Yellow, Red, Blue, Green)—how they show up, strengths, and potential overextensions citeturn1search2.  
- The **three personas** framework—Your natural (Underlying), daily (Everyday), and “too-much-of-a-good-thing” (Overextended) behaviors citeturn1search7turn1search16.  
- How these aspects mesh into your personal portrait, to boost self-awareness and guide behavior adaptation with others citeturn1search3turn1search7.  

Basically, it’s the heart of Lumina Spark—the juicy overview that maps your energy profile and personas so you can stop being clueless about yourself.

Want a breakdown of those colors or how to use this in real-life? Or should we jump to the next one and roll our eyes?
